<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbe0c6fea-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s7384w"><num value="7384w">§ 7384w.</num><heading> Subpoenas; oaths; examination of witnesses</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Labor, with respect to any matter under this part, may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbe0c6feb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s7384w/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> issue subpoenas for and compel the attendance of witnesses;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbe0c6fec-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s7384w/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> administer oaths;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbe0c6fed-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s7384w/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> examine witnesses; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbe0c6fee-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s7384w/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> require the production of books, papers, documents, and other evidence.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbe0c6fef-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/398/s1/dC/tXXXVI/s3632">Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [div. C, title XXXVI, § 3632]</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/108/375/dC/tXXXI/s3163/a">Pub. L. 108–375, div. C, title XXXI, § 3163(a)</ref>, <date date="2004-10-28">Oct. 28, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/2186">118 Stat. 2186</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
